description.narrative: In 2019, UNICEF support for MNCH interventions and services centered on improving the quality of and scaling-up access to maternal, newborn and child health services. Through UNICEF support, the MOH introduced Rotavirus vaccine into the routine immunization program nationally and provided procurement services for vaccines and vaccine-consumables and measles outbreak response. UNICEF also built the capacity of health professionals on different service packages including IMNCI (80 HWs in 4 municipalities), Essential newborn care (40 HWs in 10 health facilities) and Safe and Clean Delivery (43 HWs in 2 municipalities), while enhancing service quality through the Continuous Quality Improvement (CQI) initiative. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/02/2020
